{"type":null,"faqId":34719,"title":" How can I share a network with computers and play games with other Bluetooth devices?","answer":"<html>\n<head>\n<META http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n<style type=\"text/css\">.b1{white-space-collapsing:preserve;}\n.d1{margin: 1.18125in 0.7875in 1.18125in 0.7875in;}\n.p1{margin-left:1.18125in;margin-top:0.11111111in;margin-bottom:0.11111111in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;}\n.p2{text-indent:-0.2951389in;margin-left:1.4763889in;margin-top:0.055555556in;margin-bottom:0.055555556in;text-align:start;hyphenate:auto;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;}\n.s1{font-weight:bold;}\n.s2{display: inline-block; text-indent: 0; min-width: 0.3048611in;}\n</style>\n</head>\n<body class=\"b1\">\n<div  >\n<p  >\n<span>Your phone can share a network with computers and play games by using Bluetooth.</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span>Your phone supports the personal area network (PAN) so that other devices can share the network resources. </span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span>Touch </span><span class=\"s1\">Settings</span><span> &gt; </span><span class=\"s1\">Moreâ€¦</span><span> &gt; </span><span class=\"s1\">Tethering &amp; portable hotspot</span><span> &gt; </span><span class=\"s1\">Bluetooth tethering</span><span>. Upon reception of the connection request from a Bluetooth device, you set up a PAN. </span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<img src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=110568\" style=\"width:1.3951389in;height:2.4826388in;vertical-align:text-bottom;\"/><span> </span><img src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=110569\" style=\"width:1.4027778in;height:2.4777777in;vertical-align:text-bottom;\"/><span> </span><img src=\"http://consumer.huawei.com/support/servlet/imageServlet?dlType=HtmlAreaImage&imageId=110570\" style=\"width:1.3875in;height:2.4743056in;vertical-align:text-bottom;\"/></p>\n<p  ></p>\n<p  >\n<span>To play games using Bluetooth, perform the following steps: (This function depends on third-party applications in most cases.)</span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span class=\"s2\">1.  </span><span>Search Bluetooth devices in the game. </span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span class=\"s2\">1.  </span><span>Pair your phone with other Bluetooth devices. </span>\n</p>\n<p  >\n<span class=\"s2\">1.  </span><span>Start the game.</span>\n</p>\n</div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":0,"unUseful":0,"languageId":244,"languageName":"mm","faqCode":"9459","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"0","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1436871807000,"seriesProductName":"H30-L02","visitedTimes":1,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":null,"filePath":null,"imagePath":null,"imageName":null,"productIdList":null,"curPage":null,"pageSize":null,"siteCode":null,"statusFlag":"Publish","returnCode":0,"totalRows":null,"keywords":"HONOR 3C LTE (H30-L02)","avgScore":0.0,"createDate":null,"totalPages":null}